  "prompt": "What is a type of energy?",
  "response": "There are several types of energy, each with unique properties and applications. Some of the most common types include:\n\n1. **Kinetic Energy**: The energy an object possesses due to its motion.\n\n2. **Potential Energy**: The stored energy in an object due to its position or state. This includes gravitational potential energy and elastic potential energy.\n\n3. **Thermal Energy**: The internal energy in substances\u2014the vibration and movement of atoms and molecules within substances.\n\n4. **Chemical Energy**: The potential energy stored in chemical bonds of molecules. It is released or absorbed during chemical reactions.\n\n5. **Electrical Energy**: The energy associated with the flow of electric charge or electrons through a conductor.\n\n6. **Nuclear Energy**: The energy stored in the nucleus of an atom, released during nuclear reactions such as fission or fusion.\n\n7. **Radiant Energy**: The energy of electromagnetic waves, encompassing visible light, radio waves, gamma rays, and X-rays.\n\n8. **Mechanical Energy**: The sum of kinetic and potential energy in an object that is used to do work.\n\n9. **Sound Energy**: The energy carried by sound waves, produced when an object vibrates.\n\nEach of these energy types can be converted from one form to another and is subject to the laws of energy conservation.",
